Babble		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural.Aura	VISIBLE:YES	DEFINE:BabbleDC|10+(HD/2)+CHA	DESC:An allip constantly mutters and whines to itself, creating a hypnotic effect.																	SOURCEPAGE:p.4	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|(60 tf., DC %1)|BabbleDC	BENEFIT:An allip constantly mutters and whines to itself, creating a hypnotic effect. All sane creatures within 60 feet of the allip must succeed on a DC %1 Will save or be fascinated for 2d4 rounds. While a target is fascinated, the allip can approach without breaking the effect, but an attack by the allip breaks the effect. This is a sonic, mind-affecting compulsion effect. Creatures that successfully save cannot be affected by the same allip's babble for 24 hours.|BabbleDC
Madness		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural		VISIBLE:YES						DESC:Anyone targeting an allip with a thought detection, mind control, or telepathic ability makes direct contact with its tortured mind and takes 1d4 points of Wisdom damage.	SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Touch of Insanity	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural		VISIBLE:YES						DESC:The touch of an allip deals 1d4 points of Wisdom damage.																				SOURCEPAGE:p.4									BENEFIT:The touch of an allip deals 1d4 points of Wisdom damage. A successful critical hit causes 1d4 points of Wisdom damage and 1 point of Wisdom drain (instead of double Wisdom damage). On each such successful attack, an allip gains 5 temporary hit points.

###Block: Ant Lion abilities
# Ability Name	Category of Ability		Type						Visible	Description															Source Page		Description of the Benefits
Sand Trap		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A giant ant lion can create a 60-foot-diameter trap in any sand or soft earth surface.	SOURCEPAGE:p.5	BENEFIT:A giant ant lion can create a 60-foot-diameter trap in any sand or soft earth surface (mechanical trap, Perception DC 15, 20 ft. deep, no damage; DC 15 Reflex to avoid; DC 20 Climb check to climb out). Creating a sand trap takes 1 hour. A giant ant lion can make an attack of opportunity against any creature that falls to the bottom of its sand trap. These creatures can move across sand traps at their normal speed and are immune to these trap effects.

###Block: Ascomoid abilities
